==German==
===Etymology===
*Likely originates from Norse mythology's [[Odin]], plus German [[Tag]], making it "Odin's Day."
*According to ''Kluge 23th. ed'', the part ''Diens'' is from a Germanic god ''Mars Thingsus'', or possibly denoting the day on which the [[Thing]] (court) is being held.
===Noun===
